author: COMSOL
description: An iron sphere is exposed to a spatially uniform background magnetic field that is sinusoidally time-varying at a frequency of 60 Hz. The frequency of the field is low enough that the skin depth is larger than the radius of the sphere. The example computes the induced currents in the sphere and the perturbation to the background field. This example uses two approaches for solving the problem and assess them by comparing the magnetic dissipation in the different domains of the model.
label: iron_sphere_bfield_02_60hz.mph
